"'''Simple Tricks'''" is a short story written by [[Chris Cassidy]] and [[Tish Eggleston Pahl]]. It was published in the ''[[Tales from the New Republic]]'' short-story anthology by [[Bantam Spectra]] in [[1999]].

==Plot summary==
A faulty [[Hyperdrive/Legends|hyperdrive]] has left the [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggling]] duo of [[Fenig Nabon]] and [[Ghitsa Dogder]] stranded on [[Prishardia]], but Ghitsa makes the most of the situation by posing as a [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] to bilk gullible locals out of goods. Ghitsa's act attracts some unwelcome attention – an underworld businessman kidnaps her due to her past dealing with the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutts]]. Ghitsa’s Jedi act has also brought [[Kyp Durron]] to Prishardia, and though Fen at first has serious misgivings about Kyp – she knows about his utter destruction of the [[Carida system/Legends|Carida system]] – the two work together to rescue Ghitsa. Fen comes to see Kyp as a [[Torture/Legends|tortured]], broken soul still healing from his past misdeeds. After her rescue, Ghitsa decides to drop the Jedi act from her repertoire, while Fen chooses to forward interesting information about Hutt dealings to her friend and colleague [[Talon Karrde]].

==Continuity==
''Simple Tricks'' hints at the funding and construction of the [[Darksaber (superweapon)|Darksaber]], and ends with [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] returning to [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]] injured. This places this tale in [[12 ABY/Legends|12 ABY]], during and after [[Children of the Jedi (novel)|''Children of the Jedi]], and prior to the [[Darksaber (novel)|''Darksaber'']].

